  "body": "# Feature Issue\r\n\r\n### User Story\r\n\r\nAs a user, I want to feel secure putting my 12-word to import an existing account.\r\n\r\n### Description\r\n\r\n![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/1106118/120034211-1bc78f80-bfd3-11eb-826a-1c52a0fabf3a.png)\r\n\r\nRight after putting the 12 words to import an existing account, users are asked to \"re-encrypt\" the keys. Users are not proceeding at this step because they think it will change their 12-words seed phrase somehow, when in fact it will just encrypt them to store securely on the phone, using the password to be able to decrypt when needed.\r\n\r\n### Acceptance Criteria\r\n\r\nWe should just make it clear, changing the copy of this screen. We have plenty of available space to make it as clear as possible.",
